The paper deals with image captioning, which is a task in computer vision (cs.CV). It also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as the captions are generated using language models. The use of constrained beam search and pretrained word embeddings suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of ground-truth labels to improve caption quality, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
